    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that seems a bit one-sided. what about the other side of that debate? like, aren't there plenty of economists who say the safety net actually helps people find better jobs by giving them some stability, or that the \"welfare trap\" is mostly a myth? it feels like u're only really giving me the argument for cutting benefits.",
