      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The counter-argument, which is often championed by progressive economists, is that the safety net acts as a crucial economic stabilizer. They argue that without a floor, people are forced to take any available, often exploitative, job just to survive. By providing a basic safety net, individuals gain the security to pursue education, start businesses, or wait for better-fitting employment, which ultimately boosts long-term economic productivity.",
